<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1436,1490,2036]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis box="[151,280,1491,1516]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Three pairs of branched branchiae, starting on segment 2 or 3, thereafter discontinuous on posterior segments; eyespots present or absent; lateral lappets absent; ventral shields from segment 1; pairs of notopodia from segment 4 along all the body; notochaeta distally serrate, twisted in posterior chaetigers; neuropodia from segment 5, uncini avicular in single rows in segments 5–9 or 10; thereafter in double rows, arranged face to face, up to the end of the body or closely the end.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="64.[151,1436,1490,2036]" lastBlockId="65.[151,1436,152,298]" lastPageId="65" lastPageNumber="66" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis box="[198,524,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Remarks: Terebellobanchia</emphasis>
has three described and valid species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rullier, 1972" authorityName="Rullier" authorityYear="1972" box="[1002,1297,1690,1716]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Terebellobanchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hugonis">
<emphasis box="[1002,1127,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">T. hugonis</emphasis>
Rullier, 1972
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry name="New Caledonia" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Day, 1951" authorityName="Day" authorityYear="1951" box="[286,569,1730,1756]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Terebellobanchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis box="[286,436,1731,1756]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">T. natalensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Day, J. H." box="[444,569,1730,1756]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 67" refId="ref60832" refString="Day, J. H. (1951) The polychaet fauna of South Africa, 1. The Intertidal and estuarine Polychaeta of Natal and Mozambique. Annals of the Natal Museum, 12, 1 - 67." type="journal article" year="1951">Day, 1951</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[649,805,1730,1756]" name="South Africa" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Londono-Mesa and Carrera-Parra, (2005)" authorityName="Londono-Mesa and Carrera-Parra" authorityYear="2005" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Terebellobranchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="mchughae">
<emphasis box="[869,1020,1731,1756]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">T. mchughae</emphasis>
Londoño-Mesa and Carrera-Parra, (2005)
</taxonomicName>
, recently described from the Mexican 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[740,865,1770,1796]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="64" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
. A fourth described species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Treadwell, 1931" authorityName=", Treadwell" authorityYear="1931" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Terebella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hiata">
<emphasis box="[1250,1435,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Terebella hiata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Treadwell, A. L." box="[151,347,1810,1836]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="79 - 81" refId="ref64800" refString="Treadwell, A. L. (1931) New terebellid annelids, Thelepus haitiensis and Terebella hiata. Zoologica, 12, 79 - 81." type="journal article" year="1931">Treadwell, 1931</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is transferred to this genus as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Treadwell, 1931)" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Treadwell" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[729,1238,1810,1836]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Terebellobranchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hiata" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis box="[729,1013,1811,1836]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Terebellobranchia hiata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Treadwell, A. L." box="[1032,1228,1810,1836]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="79 - 81" refId="ref64800" refString="Treadwell, A. L. (1931) New terebellid annelids, Thelepus haitiensis and Terebella hiata. Zoologica, 12, 79 - 81." type="journal article" year="1931">Treadwell, 1931</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1248,1380,1810,1836]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The genus was initially erected for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Day" authorityYear="1951" box="[510,658,1851,1876]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Terebellobanchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="natalensis">
<emphasis box="[510,658,1851,1876]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">T. natalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with branchiae on segments 3, 7 and 13, notopodia from segment 4, and neuropodia from segment 5 (
<bibRefCitation author="Day, J. H." box="[586,715,1890,1916]" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" pagination="1 - 67" refId="ref60832" refString="Day, J. H. (1951) The polychaet fauna of South Africa, 1. The Intertidal and estuarine Polychaeta of Natal and Mozambique. Annals of the Natal Museum, 12, 1 - 67." type="journal article" year="1951">Day, 1951</bibRefCitation>
). Nevertheless, the relative position of the second and third pairs of branchiae as well as the first pair of notopodia differ in the included species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rullier" authorityYear="1972" box="[1147,1269,1931,1956]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Terebellobanchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hugonis">
<emphasis box="[1147,1269,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">T. hugonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has branchiae on segments 3, 4 and 7, notopodia from segment 3 and neuropodia from segment 
<quantity box="[1136,1182,1970,1996]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" unit="in" value="4.0">4 in</quantity>
double rows along 6 segments; 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Londono-Mesa and Carrera-Parra" authorityYear="2005" box="[276,618,2011,2036]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Terebellobranchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="64" pageNumber="65" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="mchughae">
<emphasis box="[276,618,2011,2036]" italics="true" pageId="64" pageNumber="65">Terebellobranchia mchughae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has branchiae on segments 3, 4 and 7, notopodia from segment 4 and neuropodia from segment 
<quantity box="[458,503,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
double rows along the next 5 segments; and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName="Treadwell" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[1028,1116,152,177]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Terebellobranchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hiata">
<emphasis box="[1028,1116,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">T. hiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has branchiae on segments 2, 5 and 8, notochaetae from segment 4 and neurochaetae from segment 
<quantity box="[1015,1061,192,218]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" unit="in" value="5.0">5 in</quantity>
double rows along 6 segments. Thus, a revision of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rullier" authorityYear="1972" box="[387,510,232,257]" class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Terebellobanchia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hugonis">
<emphasis box="[387,510,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">T. hugonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is required in order to elucidate whether this species has notopodia and neuropodia from segments 3–4, or from segments 4–5, respectively.
</paragraph>
